// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_RogToHero_SL8-9_Task_07 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - CrybabyHero 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2987542613" "<color orange>The Crab Spider Webmaster throws its arms and spider legs up.</color><br><br>Alright, I'll tell you whatever you want to know, just stop beating me!"
// Answer Text :
"P4051780154" "Where is Savage Siren?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1363639129" "She's all the way in the back, but we've got Black Scorpion's security here. You'll never be able to get through all of them, not when it's that heavily fortified!<br><br><color orange>You'll need to figure out a way to lure out the patrols one by one. Perhaps by activating an emergency alarm of some sorts.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P882500031" "Where's the alarm system located?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P4160052832" "<color orange>The Webmaster gives you the details of where you can find the alarm system for the base. You'll just need to activate it and beat down the incoming guards in order to soften up the defense around Savage Siren.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2429349226" "(Knock out the Webmaster)"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P4257720609" "<color orange>You knock out the Webmaster. Time to head towards that alarm system!</color>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - CrybabyHeroAgain 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2594457703" "{HeroName}... Why did you save me? I don't have any money or anything to give you. You do understand that, right? You won't be getting <i>anything</i> out of this."
// Answer Text :
"P4242525612" "Just tell your client to keep putting out contracts on Arachnos."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P4054499127" "Alright. But I think you're getting soft. <i>I</i> would've never rescued you for free, even if it meant losing a client. But I guess that's what makes me different from you, isn't it?"
// Answer Text :
"P1613570532" "... You're welcome."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2496871878" "Paragon City might be bringing out the pro-bono side of you. There isn't much money to be made <i>now</i> by saving Savage Siren's life, but you'll be able to stick it to Arachnos whenever you like in the future and earn a good paycheck from it.<br><br>You're able to easily locate the 'secret' Arachnos base in Paragon where they're holding her. You could get there quick enough to find Savage Siren and get her out of there."
// AcceptString :
"P3443815404" "Save Savage Siren"
// SendOffString :
"P2255126769" "You use the deactivated Arachnos Spider to pinpoint the exact location of the Arachnos base. Time to make your move and ensure that there's money to be made in the future."
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2775370908" "You'll have to move if you're going to recover Savage Siren in time!"
// TaskTitle :
"P3994167128" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Deactivated Arachnos Spider</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2837403054" "You manage to get in to the Arachnos base, though there's still more to be done before this job is over."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2970357229" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Deactivated Arachnos Spider</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Savage Siren wasn't exactly thankful for your rescue, but you never really expected someone like her to be.<br><br>Though, what she said still rings in your mind. Is she right that you're starting to grow soft? Is being around Paragon really starting to rub off on how you act?"

