// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_RogToHero_SL8-9_Task_09 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - ScryingGlyph 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1305641324" "<color orange>You access the Vanguard computer and pull up the schematics of the base. You're able to find where General Aarons is, though unfortunately he's surrounded by IDF soldiers. You're also able to locate the mainframe where Vanguard has the majority of its information.<br><br>You download all the information you can, though you may want to get rid of this computer to prevent the Praetorians from getting this information as well."
// Answer Text :
"P4162662593" "(Destroy the Vanguard computer)"
// Page InformationPage5 Text :
"P2703085863" "<color orange>Just as you are turning to leave you hear a vocal alarm raised by the Arachnos forces inside the ruins. Apparently they too felt the magic of the Scrying Glyphs dissipate and they are headed your way!</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2311663164" "Leave quickly!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4082842749" "The Praetorians must've gotten the drop on Vanguard if they managed to take one of their bases. Vanguard soldiers are known for being <i>very</i> tough in a fight, given the experience they have fighting off the Rikti.<br><br>It might be a bit of a fight, you versus Emperor Cole's Imperial Defense Force, but at least it'll mean you can still continue to work safely in the future"
// AcceptString :
"P1539358577" "Save General Aarons and Vanguard"
// SendOffString :
"P369419390" "You're able to pull up the location of the base without too much difficulty. This time, the Praetorians will be the ones getting the surprise ambush."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3939055262" "Rescue General Aarons from the IDF"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1875221532" "General Aarons has precious little time, you have to hurry!"
// TaskTitle :
"P1190008291" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Hologram of General Aarons</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P4055968418" "You spotted some knocked out Vanguard soldiers as you walked in. The IDF are here in force. You'll have to access a Vanguard computer to try to get a hold of the situation."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2370008272" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Hologram of General Aarons</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>General Aarons gives you a salute before walking off.<br><br>He doesn't seem to be a man to mince words, but at least the job is done. Well, it wasn't really so much a job as it was a rescue operation. How many more of these can you do? Or, is this something you might actually <i>enjoy</i> doing?"

